1
00:00:00,020 --> 00:00:03,760
[All characters, behaviors, locations,
organizations, professions, and events

2
00:00:03,780 --> 00:00:07,510
shown in this series are entirely fictional,
created solely for entertainment purposes,

3
00:00:07,530 --> 00:00:11,260
with no intention of instructing
or endorsing any kind of behaviors;

4
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:15,010
viewer discretion is advised]

5
00:00:15,690 --> 00:00:18,210
I always make everything worse.

6
00:00:19,340 --> 00:00:20,410
It's my fault...

7
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:23,880
What happened last night

8
00:00:23,910 --> 00:00:25,810
shouldn't have happened to anyone,

9
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:26,740
whether it was me,

10
00:00:26,770 --> 00:00:27,880
the others on the farm,

11
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,090
or you.

12
00:00:32,820 --> 00:00:35,290
This place is like your home now.

13
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:42,310
Mr. Sila,

14
00:00:42,420 --> 00:00:44,590
can you come to
the meeting room right away?

15
00:00:44,710 --> 00:00:47,090
There's an important guest
who wants to meet you.

16
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:02,150
Hello.

17
00:01:06,110 --> 00:01:07,810
Is there something important

18
00:01:09,930 --> 00:01:13,760
that requires the head of Khum Rimpha
to come all the way here?

19
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:18,590
It's nothing serious.

20
00:01:20,460 --> 00:01:22,530
I'm just here to congratulate you.

21
00:01:24,890 --> 00:01:27,000
I've heard that Phusangdao Farm

22
00:01:27,050 --> 00:01:28,990
is about to close the deal with K Group.

23
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:36,560
Congratulations.

24
00:01:38,150 --> 00:01:38,979
My friend...

25
00:01:49,350 --> 00:01:50,600
These flowers are pretty.

26
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:54,620
We've known each other for a long time now.

27
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:58,100
And since you're like family to me,

28
00:01:59,140 --> 00:02:00,670
I'd like to give you some advice.

29
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:04,200
Business is like a game.

30
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:06,540
Whoever has the upper hand

31
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:08,880
gets the benefits.

32
00:02:10,300 --> 00:02:11,850
But don't let your guard down.

33
00:02:12,710 --> 00:02:14,300
Because when you fall,

34
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:17,530
the one who gets hurt

35
00:02:18,630 --> 00:02:19,880
is you.

36
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,120
Mr. Sila.

37
00:02:34,090 --> 00:02:34,800
What is it?

38
00:02:35,260 --> 00:02:37,190
Our partner just emailed me

39
00:02:37,620 --> 00:02:40,160
that the deal will have to
be postponed indefinitely.

40
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,400
According to them,
further review is required

41
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,090
due to issues with the figures.

42
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:56,730
I think...

43
00:02:57,110 --> 00:02:59,960
maybe you're not quite ready
to play this game yet.

44
00:03:00,710 --> 00:03:02,400
How did you manage to screw up

45
00:03:03,910 --> 00:03:05,690
a simple deal like this?

46
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,920
I would've been so ashamed.

47
00:03:12,820 --> 00:03:15,010
Some people only know how to play dirty

48
00:03:15,810 --> 00:03:18,310
and are too cowardly to face the truth.

49
00:03:21,070 --> 00:03:22,630
Is this impressive to you?

50
00:03:24,710 --> 00:03:26,190
Because I think it's pathetic.

51
00:03:27,810 --> 00:03:29,579
When you play dirty,

52
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:32,890
it will come back to bite you.

53
00:03:33,590 --> 00:03:34,570
Remember that.

54
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:43,090
It seems

55
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,920
you're a bit tied up,

56
00:03:45,990 --> 00:03:49,000
so Muang and I won't keep you any longer.

57
00:03:51,110 --> 00:03:51,910
Oh,

58
00:03:52,410 --> 00:03:54,450
if you need any help from Khum Rimpha,

59
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,200
you can let me know.

60
00:04:38,590 --> 00:04:43,580
♫But no one sees what's behind my smiles♫

61
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,640
♫It's the loneliness I try to hide♫

62
00:04:47,670 --> 00:04:53,030
♫Will there be someone my heart's seeking?♫

63
00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:56,900
♫Then today, I got you near♫

64
00:04:56,930 --> 00:05:01,680
♫You made my heart drift away,♫

65
00:05:01,710 --> 00:05:03,660
♫lost in your gaze♫

66
00:05:03,990 --> 00:05:07,140
♫Like a stream washing over me♫

67
00:05:07,170 --> 00:05:12,620
♫Wanna give this a try,
like it's more than one night?♫

68
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:16,230
♫Let's change one night♫

69
00:05:16,270 --> 00:05:18,050
♫into something more, alright♫

70
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:21,200
♫Let's follow our hearts once♫

71
00:05:21,260 --> 00:05:27,090
♫Wanna give this a try,
just let me get inside?♫

72
00:05:27,150 --> 00:05:33,310
♫Deep inside, I'll make you feel whole♫

73
00:05:33,550 --> 00:05:37,890
♫May I ask you to be my last?♫

74
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,540
[Phusangdao]

75
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:11,300
You're awfully loyal to the family,
aren't you, Chakkrit?

76
00:06:12,090 --> 00:06:14,280
You and your father

77
00:06:14,910 --> 00:06:16,010
are exactly alike.

78
00:06:17,870 --> 00:06:20,260
Except your father

79
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:22,120
is a little smarter than you.

80
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:26,340
If I were you,
I'd pick the obviously better choice.

81
00:06:26,420 --> 00:06:27,720
But I don't think

82
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:30,710
you'd want to be
an underling your whole life,

83
00:06:31,820 --> 00:06:32,820
would you?

84
00:06:33,550 --> 00:06:34,550
Haven't you considered

85
00:06:36,540 --> 00:06:37,810
that maybe

86
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,500
you deserve more than this?

87
00:06:41,530 --> 00:06:43,040
My duty

88
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:45,610
is to protect this farm.

89
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,130
Call it what you like,

90
00:06:49,170 --> 00:06:50,100
but I know

91
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:52,100
what I'm doing.

92
00:06:53,350 --> 00:06:56,280
But are you sure
the person you're protecting

93
00:06:56,590 --> 00:06:59,120
still deserves your loyalty?

94
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:02,220
Chiang Rai isn't that big.

95
00:07:02,810 --> 00:07:04,500
There's nowhere
my influence doesn’t reach.

96
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:08,020
Perhaps it might be

97
00:07:08,070 --> 00:07:09,490
even bigger than you think.

98
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,000
I won't let whoever tries to destroy

99
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:16,920
this work get away with it.

100
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:21,870
Oh.

101
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,000
Give my regards to your Boss.

102
00:07:25,190 --> 00:07:26,930
Tell him I have a surprise for him.

103
00:07:31,550 --> 00:07:32,620
I'll see him at the Summit.

104
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,320
Don't cry, alright?

105
00:08:33,620 --> 00:08:34,980
I'm here now.

106
00:09:53,210 --> 00:09:54,100
Are you awake?

107
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:58,680
How are you?

108
00:10:00,620 --> 00:10:02,280
Are you feeling any better?

109
00:10:06,420 --> 00:10:07,420
I feel better now.

110
00:10:08,410 --> 00:10:09,050
But...

111
00:10:13,140 --> 00:10:14,690
You don't have to push yourself.

112
00:10:16,290 --> 00:10:18,000
It's okay

113
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:19,610
if you still need time.

114
00:10:25,610 --> 00:10:27,100
Thank you, Sila.

115
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,320
I can't believe

116
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:38,410
I truly deserve your love like this.

117
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:46,030
I think...

118
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:50,930
everyone deserves to be loved, Saitharn.

119
00:10:53,230 --> 00:10:55,090
It's easy for you to say that.

120
00:10:56,970 --> 00:10:58,090
But I'm scared.

121
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:03,980
I've been hurt before
because I believed in it.

122
00:11:10,410 --> 00:11:12,810
Then let me prove it.

123
00:11:17,930 --> 00:11:19,400
Not with words

124
00:11:22,910 --> 00:11:23,910
but with time.

125
00:11:29,410 --> 00:11:30,780
Don't you hate me?

126
00:11:33,690 --> 00:11:35,420
I'm not that good a person, you know?

127
00:11:59,150 --> 00:12:00,190
Saitharn,

128
00:12:04,630 --> 00:12:06,500
you may say bad things about yourself.

129
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:10,910
You can blame yourself
as much as you want.

130
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:17,420
But I want you to know
I would never judge you by your past

131
00:12:17,450 --> 00:12:19,240
or what you've been through.

132
00:12:24,850 --> 00:12:28,300
The Saitharn I'm with right now

133
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:31,990
has shown me

134
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:34,390
he isn't a bad person.

135
00:12:39,690 --> 00:12:42,510
And everything that happened
isn't your fault.

136
00:12:44,170 --> 00:12:45,800
But I already said

137
00:12:45,930 --> 00:12:46,810
- that I...
- Saitharn.

138
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:52,000
You can believe that if you want,

139
00:12:56,690 --> 00:12:59,100
but I'll be here

140
00:12:59,290 --> 00:13:01,390
to remind you it's not your fault.

141
00:13:06,490 --> 00:13:08,600
I'll keep reminding you

142
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:13,190
until you believe me.

143
00:13:29,990 --> 00:13:32,310
I don't know if you'll
believe what I'm saying,

144
00:13:38,810 --> 00:13:40,890
but I promise

145
00:13:42,310 --> 00:13:46,210
I won't let anyone make
you feel worthless again.

146
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:56,320
I promise.

147
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:11,890
♫I wanna thank you for making me feel♫

148
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:15,580
♫Just how beautiful love can be♫

149
00:14:15,660 --> 00:14:17,810
♫Every chamber of my heart♫

150
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:20,510
♫Will be yours from now on♫

151
00:14:20,550 --> 00:14:26,100
♫You're a godsent present from above♫

152
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:32,150
♫I'll always belong to you evermore♫

153
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:37,610
♫My heart will always be yours forever♫

154
00:14:54,100 --> 00:14:55,440
Mok, let me come with you.

155
00:14:55,460 --> 00:14:56,310
What?

156
00:14:56,330 --> 00:14:57,620
Don't follow me!

157
00:14:58,310 --> 00:15:01,000
Let me join you.
I don't want to stay at my place alone.

158
00:15:01,290 --> 00:15:03,230
I'm getting you your meal.
I have to hurry.

159
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,430
Let me come with you, please.

160
00:15:04,830 --> 00:15:05,410
Please.

161
00:15:05,770 --> 00:15:06,300
Hey.

162
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:09,490
Are you good?

163
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:12,120
Come on. Let's head back.

164
00:15:12,890 --> 00:15:13,890
You're not heading out there?

165
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:15,380
It's okay. I'll come for it another time.

166
00:15:15,410 --> 00:15:16,190
Let's get you back first.

167
00:15:16,220 --> 00:15:17,800
I don't want to be there alone.

168
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:22,550
[Phusangdao Group]

169
00:15:22,580 --> 00:15:24,100
Phae, look at this.

170
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:25,280
Hm?

171
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:27,810
Let me have a look.

172
00:15:30,140 --> 00:15:31,140
Whoa.

173
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:35,620
It's gorgeous.

174
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:41,720
Gorgeous.

175
00:15:45,590 --> 00:15:46,820
Thank you, Gale,

176
00:15:47,390 --> 00:15:50,030
for letting me be part of this project.

177
00:15:52,550 --> 00:15:54,410
It's me who needs to thank you, Phae.

178
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,820
You've helped me so much that
you haven't caught a break.

179
00:15:58,350 --> 00:15:59,390
On top of that,

180
00:16:00,990 --> 00:16:02,300
without you,

181
00:16:03,030 --> 00:16:05,410
it wouldn't turn out this perfect.

182
00:16:09,650 --> 00:16:11,690
You're really amazing, you know?

183
00:16:12,590 --> 00:16:14,510
Really?

184
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:19,370
I don't know.

185
00:16:19,410 --> 00:16:20,410
I...

186
00:16:24,830 --> 00:16:26,780
I've never been confident in myself.

187
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:29,590
I don't know

188
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:32,880
if I can truly be good at anything.

189
00:16:34,260 --> 00:16:35,500
That's why I want to find out

190
00:16:35,850 --> 00:16:37,510
whether your compliment

191
00:16:37,850 --> 00:16:39,910
was just out of politeness

192
00:16:40,210 --> 00:16:41,490
or genuinely because of my talent.

193
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:54,590
I don't know

194
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:56,400
how much

195
00:16:56,610 --> 00:16:59,110
your achievements have been ignored,

196
00:17:01,910 --> 00:17:02,910
but right here

197
00:17:03,860 --> 00:17:04,890
and right now,

198
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:08,500
I do feel that you are talented.

199
00:17:14,369 --> 00:17:16,500
For every compliment you didn't receive,

200
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:19,089
you shall receive all of it from me.

201
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:26,300
I'll reassure you

202
00:17:27,859 --> 00:17:28,910
how valuable

203
00:17:28,940 --> 00:17:30,800
you truly are,

204
00:17:35,190 --> 00:17:36,190
in my eyes

205
00:17:39,710 --> 00:17:41,000
at least.

206
00:17:46,230 --> 00:17:47,700
If that's the case...

207
00:17:47,860 --> 00:17:49,670
can you promise me

208
00:17:50,130 --> 00:17:50,820
that you'll...

209
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:54,010
always be right by my side
to compliment me?

210
00:17:56,870 --> 00:17:57,300
Hm?

211
00:17:58,700 --> 00:17:59,490
I promise.

212
00:18:27,690 --> 00:18:28,690
Thank you.

213
00:18:54,350 --> 00:18:57,650
Have you ever thought about how Sila and I
gave you the chance to work here again?

214
00:18:57,740 --> 00:18:59,640
This project decides
the future of Phusangdao Group.

215
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:01,980
If we fail again, the deal will not be
the only thing we will lose.

216
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:04,310
Ms. Wipa, we have already rechecked.

217
00:19:04,550 --> 00:19:06,240
You are making up an excuse
after we lost the deal?

218
00:19:06,280 --> 00:19:08,120
We are not, but it's not our fault.

219
00:19:08,150 --> 00:19:09,050
The statistics team...

220
00:19:09,080 --> 00:19:10,460
It's not our fault.

221
00:19:10,520 --> 00:19:13,300
It's the marketing team's fault
for failing to carefully check the details.

222
00:19:13,430 --> 00:19:14,500
So what?

223
00:19:14,540 --> 00:19:15,970
You guys are in the same boat!

224
00:19:16,010 --> 00:19:16,870
What are you guys doing?

225
00:19:16,910 --> 00:19:18,200
Do you think shifting blame will help?

226
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,100
But Ms. Wipa,

227
00:19:19,140 --> 00:19:20,760
if we don't have the data
from the management,

228
00:19:20,990 --> 00:19:22,560
we won't have anything to compare.

229
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:23,490
That is an excuse.

230
00:19:23,710 --> 00:19:26,090
Why didn't you recheck the details
before the submission?

231
00:19:26,810 --> 00:19:28,590
You always throw things at us.

232
00:19:28,710 --> 00:19:30,140
You dare say that to me?!

233
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:31,970
If I weren't the project coordinator,

234
00:19:32,010 --> 00:19:33,590
you wouldn't know
anything about the partner.

235
00:19:33,630 --> 00:19:36,250
But we've been overworked for
the entire month now, Ms. Wipa.

236
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:38,240
It was just a minor mistake.

237
00:19:38,290 --> 00:19:40,020
Why are you putting all the blame on us?

238
00:19:40,050 --> 00:19:41,110
"A minor mistake"?

239
00:19:41,390 --> 00:19:43,840
Losing a multi-million-baht deal
is a minor mistake?

240
00:19:44,040 --> 00:19:46,090
Who was the one submitting
the files to the partner?

241
00:19:46,270 --> 00:19:46,980
Silence!

242
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:51,230
I require every team
to recheck every page and every number.

243
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,710
There must be zero margin for error.

244
00:19:59,050 --> 00:20:00,090
Yes, Mr. Sila.

245
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,510
If we fail a simple task such as this,

246
00:20:03,170 --> 00:20:05,570
how, then, would we fare
against Khum Rimpha?

247
00:20:07,090 --> 00:20:09,080
You may all return to your work now.

248
00:20:26,690 --> 00:20:27,340
Ms. Wipa.

249
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,390
Do you know

250
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:33,110
who is behind this mess?

251
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:38,210
It can only be those from Khum Rimpha.

252
00:20:40,830 --> 00:20:42,610
I will gather evidence for us.

253
00:20:42,840 --> 00:20:44,070
They won't wiggle their way out.

254
00:20:53,450 --> 00:20:54,480
Mr. Sila.

255
00:20:56,330 --> 00:20:57,890
I would like you to think about this.

256
00:20:57,970 --> 00:20:59,270
Aside from me,

257
00:20:59,570 --> 00:21:02,010
who else is always right by your side?

258
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:25,760
Is there a problem, Boss?

259
00:21:28,650 --> 00:21:29,690
You know

260
00:21:31,010 --> 00:21:32,090
the culprit behind this, don't you?

261
00:21:36,220 --> 00:21:37,180
I do.

262
00:21:38,220 --> 00:21:40,860
And I have already coordinated
with the local police.

263
00:21:41,990 --> 00:21:43,510
They won't get away with this.

264
00:21:44,400 --> 00:21:45,790
That is not what I meant.

265
00:21:50,170 --> 00:21:51,430
If such is the case...

266
00:21:52,430 --> 00:21:54,170
what is it you are referring to?

267
00:21:54,660 --> 00:21:56,610
Can you help me with something?

268
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:58,910
Of course.

269
00:22:00,430 --> 00:22:02,700
It is my duty to serve you.

270
00:22:03,650 --> 00:22:06,000
So you are going to do

271
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:10,570
whatever I say, correct?

272
00:22:11,620 --> 00:22:12,640
Certainly.

273
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:16,110
Good.

274
00:22:18,170 --> 00:22:19,980
Then I have something for you to do.

275
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:25,520
It is something that only you can do.

276
00:23:41,620 --> 00:23:42,620
I knew it.

277
00:23:42,730 --> 00:23:43,730
It has to be you.

278
00:23:44,510 --> 00:23:45,480
Nonsense.

279
00:23:45,510 --> 00:23:47,610
How can anyone tell
who it is just from a knock on the door?

280
00:23:49,890 --> 00:23:51,610
Not just a knock on the door, though.

281
00:23:52,310 --> 00:23:54,500
I even recognize the sound of you breathing.

282
00:23:54,910 --> 00:23:55,910
Righto.

283
00:23:56,300 --> 00:23:57,520
Sila, a man with a sixth sense.

284
00:23:59,970 --> 00:24:01,020
Right. Here.

285
00:24:01,510 --> 00:24:02,810
I'm bringing you some tea.

286
00:24:03,550 --> 00:24:05,200
I brewed it myself, by the way.

287
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:08,040
I even sorted each tea leaf myself.

288
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:11,700
You must've been hard at work on this.

289
00:24:12,310 --> 00:24:14,810
No wonder I could smell
the aroma right from the door.

290
00:24:19,040 --> 00:24:20,090
Here you go.

291
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:22,710
Oh, it smells delightful.

292
00:24:23,030 --> 00:24:24,180
Try it for yourself.

293
00:24:30,080 --> 00:24:30,610
Hey!

294
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:31,340
Hm.

295
00:24:31,450 --> 00:24:33,440
Did you dump
a whole sugar factory in the cup?

296
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:34,520
It's too sweet?

297
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:36,130
I'll brew you a new cup, then.

298
00:24:36,830 --> 00:24:37,610
No need.

299
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:43,200
Hey, what are you doing?

300
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:45,090
Others might see us.

301
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:46,220
It's still in the middle of the day.

302
00:24:47,540 --> 00:24:49,300
So I can do this to you at night?

303
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:51,680
Oh, I need to write that down.

304
00:24:52,450 --> 00:24:52,820
Hey!

305
00:24:52,860 --> 00:24:53,410
Whoa.

306
00:24:54,010 --> 00:24:56,010
You turn into a perverted old man again.

307
00:24:58,330 --> 00:24:59,860
Aww...

308
00:25:08,260 --> 00:25:10,330
I really want you to be by my side.

309
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:14,210
Right now, my head...

310
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:17,210
It's full of thoughts.

311
00:25:22,330 --> 00:25:22,990
Hey.

312
00:25:24,230 --> 00:25:25,600
Share them with me.

313
00:25:26,820 --> 00:25:27,480
But...

314
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:29,490
I don't think I can help much.

315
00:25:30,420 --> 00:25:31,700
I simply want to care for you.

316
00:25:39,090 --> 00:25:41,210
I'm currently suspicious of someone.

317
00:25:41,250 --> 00:25:42,010
Mm.

318
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:46,490
Every clue points to that person,

319
00:25:47,360 --> 00:25:48,600
but I don't want to believe it,

320
00:25:49,670 --> 00:25:51,730
as I once trusted that person.

321
00:25:53,990 --> 00:25:54,900
And...

322
00:25:56,590 --> 00:25:58,000
How much do you trust this individual?

323
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:02,580
A whole lot,

324
00:26:03,660 --> 00:26:05,700
as if this person is part of my family.

325
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:08,530
Mm...

326
00:26:11,450 --> 00:26:12,450
I think

327
00:26:13,530 --> 00:26:15,880
it's normal to be suspicious of someone.

328
00:26:16,430 --> 00:26:17,680
But don't forget

329
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:19,920
how much you've been through with them.

330
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:27,700
You need to consider
the past for it to be fair.

331
00:26:33,290 --> 00:26:35,640
I didn't know you could come up with
something like this.

332
00:26:37,270 --> 00:26:39,290
I copied it and noted it down here.

333
00:26:46,700 --> 00:26:47,720
Thank you.

334
00:26:49,290 --> 00:26:50,690
Feeling better?

335
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:54,000
It's better,

336
00:26:56,100 --> 00:26:59,010
but I still can't find a way out of this.

337
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:03,000
You're thinking too much.

338
00:27:03,620 --> 00:27:05,630
You're not that old to be doing that.

339
00:27:06,820 --> 00:27:08,690
The simplest solution

340
00:27:09,100 --> 00:27:11,400
is to deal with the root of the problem.

341
00:27:14,090 --> 00:27:15,090
How so?

342
00:27:17,050 --> 00:27:18,810
Think back to

343
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:22,510
what made you suspicious
of the person in the first place.

344
00:27:23,490 --> 00:27:24,400
I think

345
00:27:24,740 --> 00:27:26,580
you can find the answer from there.

346
00:27:28,260 --> 00:27:31,980
"What made me suspicious of that person?"

347
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:44,210
What do you think?

348
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:45,110
Have you figured out

349
00:27:45,810 --> 00:27:46,920
how it started?

350
00:27:47,630 --> 00:27:48,370
I've figured it out.

351
00:27:49,770 --> 00:27:51,100
Now, I know

352
00:27:51,290 --> 00:27:52,810
where I should begin.

353
00:27:53,650 --> 00:27:55,400
If you say that the answer

354
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:57,820
lies within the root of the problem,

355
00:27:59,840 --> 00:28:02,270
I simply have to look for it there.

356
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:18,100
You haven't lost your touch, Dad.

357
00:28:19,710 --> 00:28:21,300
It's been ages since you last played,

358
00:28:21,880 --> 00:28:23,100
but your shots are still
more accurate than mine.

359
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:27,390
I first played golf when I was thirteen.

360
00:28:28,190 --> 00:28:29,090
What about you?

361
00:28:30,320 --> 00:28:31,320
When did you start?

362
00:28:32,550 --> 00:28:33,180
Well...

363
00:28:33,830 --> 00:28:35,920
When I was about twenty, I think.

364
00:28:36,270 --> 00:28:37,720
Back when I was still in university,

365
00:28:38,210 --> 00:28:39,590
and you brought me along.

366
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:40,370
Hmph...

367
00:28:40,700 --> 00:28:42,120
It's only seven years.

368
00:28:43,370 --> 00:28:45,100
But that small gap

369
00:28:45,490 --> 00:28:47,310
can decide who's in the lead

370
00:28:47,340 --> 00:28:48,410
and who falls behind.

371
00:28:54,940 --> 00:28:56,310
Just like Sila,

372
00:28:57,140 --> 00:28:58,800
who learned the ropes from a young age.

373
00:29:00,090 --> 00:29:01,880
That's why he surpasses you in every way.

374
00:29:02,930 --> 00:29:03,800
And you?

375
00:29:04,120 --> 00:29:05,510
You're always his inferior.

376
00:29:08,790 --> 00:29:11,190
But isn't Sila about to fail miserably?

377
00:29:12,890 --> 00:29:14,810
Khum Rimpha is about to

378
00:29:15,490 --> 00:29:17,630
seal the deal in his place.

379
00:29:17,810 --> 00:29:19,600
His investments will go to waste.

380
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:21,190
That's because of me.

381
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:24,810
I was the one who sent in the spy.

382
00:29:25,620 --> 00:29:26,620
If it weren't for that,

383
00:29:27,030 --> 00:29:28,030
do you really think

384
00:29:28,610 --> 00:29:30,090
we'd be having the last laugh like this?

385
00:29:32,340 --> 00:29:32,970
Yes...

386
00:29:36,760 --> 00:29:39,190
This will be the last time
I ask for your help.

387
00:29:40,930 --> 00:29:42,160
After this,

388
00:29:43,890 --> 00:29:45,800
I'll fight him on my own.

389
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:47,590
You can't catch up to him.

390
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:50,900
He won't let you destroy him that easily.

391
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:56,600
As long as I can win,

392
00:29:57,190 --> 00:29:59,200
I'll use any method I can.

393
00:29:59,810 --> 00:30:01,500
Just like you've always done.

394
00:30:04,020 --> 00:30:05,610
That's my son.

395
00:30:07,710 --> 00:30:09,080
I'm confident this time.

396
00:30:10,390 --> 00:30:12,190
But I need your trump card.

397
00:30:13,820 --> 00:30:15,100
I know

398
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:17,620
you have someone working for you.

399
00:30:19,420 --> 00:30:20,920
But I really don't know who it is.

400
00:30:22,610 --> 00:30:24,890
It's all going to be over soon.

401
00:30:25,710 --> 00:30:27,290
Can't you just tell me now?

402
00:30:28,590 --> 00:30:29,970
Once everything is settled,

403
00:30:30,670 --> 00:30:31,670
you'll know.

404
00:30:33,570 --> 00:30:35,850
But for now, just know that

405
00:30:36,020 --> 00:30:38,120
it's someone close to Sila.

406
00:31:00,700 --> 00:31:01,660
Boss.

407
00:31:02,150 --> 00:31:03,240
Mr. Manmuang.

408
00:31:03,940 --> 00:31:04,580
What?

409
00:31:42,830 --> 00:31:44,370
You wanted to see me so badly

410
00:31:45,590 --> 00:31:48,000
you had to send someone to fetch me,

411
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:49,200
my friend?

412
00:31:49,370 --> 00:31:50,070
Friend?

413
00:31:51,460 --> 00:31:53,700
How many years has it been
since you last called me that?

414
00:31:57,680 --> 00:32:00,320
Ever since you refused to marry Mueanphae

415
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:01,880
because you were...

416
00:32:04,440 --> 00:32:05,390
Gay?

417
00:32:06,620 --> 00:32:07,990
Mm... gay.

418
00:32:10,010 --> 00:32:11,400
Why hesitate to say that word?

419
00:32:12,130 --> 00:32:13,080
Just say it,

420
00:32:14,510 --> 00:32:15,510
no need to be scared.

421
00:32:17,540 --> 00:32:19,720
You've always been a coward.

422
00:32:20,990 --> 00:32:23,280
You’ve never been better than me at anything,

423
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:26,690
no matter how badly your father
wants you to be.

424
00:32:26,870 --> 00:32:28,910
This stupid deal is going to end soon.

425
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:31,190
When that time comes, you'll know

426
00:32:31,910 --> 00:32:33,590
if the victor is going to be me or you.

427
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:36,540
You're the root of every problem.

428
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:39,390
I used to see you as my friend.

429
00:32:39,900 --> 00:32:40,950
As my brother.

430
00:32:41,730 --> 00:32:43,110
I f*cking trusted you.

431
00:32:43,550 --> 00:32:45,190
Is this really how you repay me?

432
00:32:45,230 --> 00:32:47,270
You're the f*cking cause
of all these problems!

433
00:32:47,790 --> 00:32:49,090
If you weren't gay,

434
00:32:49,120 --> 00:32:50,690
if you had married Mueanphae,

435
00:32:50,890 --> 00:32:52,630
do you think our families
would've ended up like this?!

436
00:32:53,010 --> 00:32:54,590
And that f*cking deal!

437
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:56,840
You're a f*cking idiot for
trusting the wrong person!

438
00:32:57,300 --> 00:32:59,510
I won't even be mad about that deal

439
00:33:00,180 --> 00:33:01,760
if you didn't play dirty

440
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:03,920
and sent those two to hurt my workers.

441
00:33:04,080 --> 00:33:04,890
What?

442
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:08,380
I just sent someone to see who
your young consort is.

443
00:33:08,950 --> 00:33:10,710
I’ve been wondering

444
00:33:11,610 --> 00:33:13,850
what's so special about him

445
00:33:14,220 --> 00:33:16,670
that you're so hooked on him.

446
00:33:16,810 --> 00:33:18,820
So hooked you sneak off
to see him at night.

447
00:33:19,830 --> 00:33:21,560
So hooked you can’t even focus on work.

448
00:33:21,870 --> 00:33:23,570
Don't you dare lay a finger on Saitharn.

449
00:33:23,860 --> 00:33:26,110
How could you hurt defenseless people?

450
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:29,510
You're f*cking pathetic.

451
00:33:30,530 --> 00:33:33,830
Your father must be very proud of
a lowly scum like you!

452
00:33:33,870 --> 00:33:36,400
At least I'm not gay,
making my father wish he were dead!

453
00:33:36,430 --> 00:33:36,860
F*cker!

454
00:33:38,870 --> 00:33:39,730
F*ck you!

455
00:33:44,490 --> 00:33:45,030
You b*stard!

456
00:33:45,120 --> 00:33:45,710
Piece of sh*t!

457
00:33:54,330 --> 00:33:55,800
Shoot me!

458
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:57,280
Shoot.

459
00:34:02,960 --> 00:34:03,690
Ow!

460
00:34:18,350 --> 00:34:19,110
Do it!

461
00:34:19,300 --> 00:34:20,800
If you think punching me...

462
00:34:21,150 --> 00:34:22,590
can help you get that deal,

463
00:34:23,940 --> 00:34:25,000
then do it!

464
00:34:36,139 --> 00:34:36,900
Ptui!

465
00:34:55,730 --> 00:34:56,580
Muang.

466
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:57,570
Hey...

467
00:34:57,740 --> 00:34:58,820
What happened to you?

468
00:34:59,290 --> 00:34:59,690
Hey!

469
00:34:59,730 --> 00:35:01,090
Let go... Phae.

470
00:35:01,130 --> 00:35:01,980
Oh, your face too.

471
00:35:04,520 --> 00:35:05,310
Let me see...

472
00:35:05,520 --> 00:35:06,910
Why are the wounds like that?

473
00:35:06,950 --> 00:35:07,800
Let go.

474
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:10,200
What did you do?

475
00:35:10,230 --> 00:35:11,310
I got into a fight with Sila.

476
00:35:13,550 --> 00:35:15,200
What? Why did you do that?

477
00:35:15,700 --> 00:35:16,990
How is Sila?

478
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:25,900
Your brother is standing here,

479
00:35:26,510 --> 00:35:28,010
bleeding in front of you,

480
00:35:30,450 --> 00:35:31,900
yet you're more concerned

481
00:35:31,950 --> 00:35:33,290
for that f*cking b*stard than me?

482
00:35:35,290 --> 00:35:37,160
We might not be related,

483
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:38,900
but he took care of me.

484
00:35:39,120 --> 00:35:41,710
He understands me better
than my real brother.

485
00:35:45,580 --> 00:35:46,580
Why?

486
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:48,240
Why...

487
00:35:49,050 --> 00:35:50,180
Why!

488
00:35:53,300 --> 00:35:55,320
Am I that f*cking terrible!?

489
00:35:58,050 --> 00:35:59,050
Huh?!

490
00:36:01,500 --> 00:36:03,790
Is that why you keep praising that f*cker?!

491
00:36:10,170 --> 00:36:11,280
Answer me!

492
00:36:15,310 --> 00:36:17,030
Just you wait, Phae.

493
00:36:18,110 --> 00:36:19,690
This upcoming Summit,

494
00:36:21,320 --> 00:36:23,580
I'll make Sila lose in front of everyone.

495
00:36:24,810 --> 00:36:28,030
I'll wipe Phusangdao Farm off the map.

496
00:36:28,660 --> 00:36:29,970
I'll make sure everyone knows

497
00:36:30,930 --> 00:36:32,710
that Sila lost to me.

498
00:36:34,090 --> 00:36:35,990
That Khum Rimpha won!

499
00:36:36,020 --> 00:36:37,400
We’re going to be back on top again!

500
00:36:43,840 --> 00:36:44,910
Do you understand me now?!

501
00:36:47,420 --> 00:36:49,600
Your brother is hurt right in front of you,

502
00:36:50,260 --> 00:36:51,910
but you still asked about that f*cker!

503
00:36:53,080 --> 00:36:53,900
Or what?

504
00:36:54,020 --> 00:36:55,560
Or do you want me to get hurt even more?!

505
00:37:00,260 --> 00:37:02,090
Why don't you go be with him, then?!

506
00:37:06,210 --> 00:37:08,610
Pack up your things and just f*cking go!

507
00:37:36,050 --> 00:37:40,830
[Chakkrit]

508
00:37:51,290 --> 00:37:52,520
Here, let me help.

509
00:37:53,290 --> 00:37:53,980
Thank you.

510
00:37:54,350 --> 00:37:55,290
Hey!

511
00:37:55,570 --> 00:37:56,170
Let me help...

512
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:57,310
What the hell, man?

513
00:37:57,340 --> 00:37:58,410
I can do it myself.

514
00:37:58,640 --> 00:37:59,290
No.

515
00:37:59,310 --> 00:38:00,950
What are you embarrassed about?

516
00:38:01,190 --> 00:38:02,590
It's nothing I've never seen.

517
00:38:03,730 --> 00:38:04,860
Get off, man...

518
00:38:05,140 --> 00:38:06,980
I'd hit you back
if your arm wasn't injured.

519
00:38:08,380 --> 00:38:09,070
Come here.

520
00:38:09,590 --> 00:38:10,500
Can you help me here?

521
00:38:10,580 --> 00:38:11,580
Yeah, gimme a sec.

522
00:38:11,690 --> 00:38:12,390
Taking this off.

523
00:38:16,700 --> 00:38:17,600
Here.

524
00:38:18,950 --> 00:38:19,450
Here.

525
00:38:24,230 --> 00:38:26,110
- It's really cold out there.
- It is...

526
00:38:26,970 --> 00:38:27,960
- Sh*t!
- Sh*t!

527
00:38:28,130 --> 00:38:29,160
- Sh*t!!
- Sh*t!

528
00:38:29,620 --> 00:38:30,620
- Sh*t!
- Shit!

529
00:38:31,810 --> 00:38:33,200
What the hell are you two doing?

530
00:38:33,410 --> 00:38:35,040
I just helped him undress

531
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:37,010
so that he could take a shower.

532
00:38:39,990 --> 00:38:40,880
Grab my towels for me.

533
00:38:40,920 --> 00:38:41,920
Alright.

534
00:38:50,420 --> 00:38:51,220
Wan.

535
00:38:51,520 --> 00:38:52,240
Hm?

536
00:38:54,840 --> 00:38:56,200
Help me bathe too, will you?

537
00:38:56,230 --> 00:38:57,970
You idiot.

538
00:38:58,320 --> 00:38:58,950
Saying things like that.

539
00:38:59,100 --> 00:39:00,790
My back is itchy, you know?

540
00:39:01,160 --> 00:39:03,110
- Go, go. Close it.
- Please, please, please?

541
00:39:03,150 --> 00:39:04,260
- Hell no.
- Aw...

542
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:13,770
[Mueanphae is calling]

543
00:39:24,110 --> 00:39:25,500
I can't sleep,

544
00:39:25,690 --> 00:39:27,410
so I want to talk to you for a bit.

545
00:39:27,810 --> 00:39:29,910
Are you sure there's nothing behind this?

546
00:39:30,600 --> 00:39:31,800
Or...

547
00:39:32,790 --> 00:39:34,350
Do you miss me?

548
00:39:34,400 --> 00:39:35,630
Are you crazy?

549
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:37,710
Answer me.

550
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:39,250
Do you miss me or not?

551
00:39:39,290 --> 00:39:41,950
Who would say such a thing, Gale?!

552
00:39:42,330 --> 00:39:44,360
It would be good if you answered it,

553
00:39:44,390 --> 00:39:45,970
as I'm actually...

554
00:39:46,750 --> 00:39:49,190
more than ready to listen
to you all night, too.

555
00:39:51,310 --> 00:39:52,700
Hearing you say that

556
00:39:52,810 --> 00:39:54,720
makes me want to stay awake even more.

557
00:39:55,110 --> 00:39:55,560
Right, right.

558
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:57,710
I'll sing you to sleep, then.

559
00:40:00,380 --> 00:40:03,130
♫Rumbling, rumbling,♫

560
00:40:03,210 --> 00:40:05,760
♫Clouds are weeping♫

561
00:40:05,790 --> 00:40:07,740
Oh, that's enough.

562
00:40:07,920 --> 00:40:09,550
The way you sing is so funny.

563
00:40:09,930 --> 00:40:10,580
What?

564
00:40:10,980 --> 00:40:12,860
It's not romantic at all?

565
00:40:12,960 --> 00:40:15,080
No, it's comical, more than anything.

566
00:40:18,300 --> 00:40:19,300
Mm...

567
00:40:22,250 --> 00:40:23,450
Actually,

568
00:40:24,390 --> 00:40:26,410
I can't sleep, not because I'm exhausted.

569
00:40:30,030 --> 00:40:31,030
But why, then?

570
00:40:32,260 --> 00:40:33,920
Is there something on your mind?

571
00:40:34,370 --> 00:40:35,370
Tonight...

572
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:37,690
I had a very terrible fight with Muang.

573
00:40:38,670 --> 00:40:41,490
He suddenly came to me

574
00:40:41,760 --> 00:40:43,030
covered in wounds.

575
00:40:43,810 --> 00:40:44,810
And...

576
00:40:45,610 --> 00:40:48,110
He said he had a fight with Sila.

577
00:40:52,690 --> 00:40:53,620
And...

578
00:40:54,200 --> 00:40:55,460
Are you okay now?

579
00:40:58,410 --> 00:40:59,410
Mm...

580
00:40:59,540 --> 00:41:01,400
I am.

581
00:41:02,040 --> 00:41:02,890
I was thinking...

582
00:41:03,230 --> 00:41:04,100
Gale.

583
00:41:06,680 --> 00:41:08,300
I have something to tell you.

584
00:41:28,310 --> 00:41:29,320
Oh, hey.

585
00:41:31,300 --> 00:41:32,080
What is it?

586
00:41:33,210 --> 00:41:34,110
What happened to you?

587
00:41:36,700 --> 00:41:38,990
Oh, I'm really sorry.

588
00:41:39,150 --> 00:41:41,720
I totally forgot
I was supposed to take you to dinner.

589
00:41:42,670 --> 00:41:44,620
Let me get changed for a minute.

590
00:41:44,740 --> 00:41:45,610
Stop.

591
00:41:47,470 --> 00:41:49,200
I'm asking you what happened to you.

592
00:41:54,100 --> 00:41:55,700
- It's just...
- Hey, there's this.

593
00:41:56,790 --> 00:41:57,790
And then here.

594
00:42:02,910 --> 00:42:03,800
Here, too.

595
00:42:04,810 --> 00:42:06,900
It's obvious you had a fight with someone.

596
00:42:08,710 --> 00:42:10,410
You're acting like a child.

597
00:42:10,970 --> 00:42:11,510
Hey...

598
00:42:11,540 --> 00:42:12,460
What happened? Tell me.

599
00:42:12,500 --> 00:42:13,300
Hey...

600
00:42:14,520 --> 00:42:15,600
Don't be like this.

601
00:42:16,390 --> 00:42:18,510
I just had a little bit of an accident.

602
00:42:20,520 --> 00:42:21,080
Huh?!

603
00:42:22,390 --> 00:42:24,880
- Did they break into the farm again?!
- Hey, calm down. Be calm.

604
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:29,330
See? I'm totally fine.

605
00:42:30,600 --> 00:42:31,700
I'm okay.

606
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:38,080
Oh, you.

607
00:42:40,200 --> 00:42:41,200
Whatever.

608
00:42:42,700 --> 00:42:44,810
Get changed and rest up already.

609
00:42:46,520 --> 00:42:48,220
Shut off your laptop and call it a night.

610
00:42:55,600 --> 00:42:56,600
I'm out of juice.

611
00:43:01,330 --> 00:43:02,840
Please let me charge myself up.

612
00:43:10,540 --> 00:43:12,010
Get some rest if you're tired.

613
00:43:24,790 --> 00:43:25,640
Hey...

614
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:51,180
Does it hurt a lot?

615
00:43:53,430 --> 00:43:55,110
Simply having you here,

616
00:43:56,550 --> 00:43:58,700
half of the pain is already gone.

617
00:44:03,650 --> 00:44:04,870
Turn around.

618
00:44:05,100 --> 00:44:06,290
I'll massage you.

619
00:44:21,640 --> 00:44:22,440
Ouch!

620
00:44:24,230 --> 00:44:26,000
You're an adult now,

621
00:44:26,290 --> 00:44:28,470
yet you got into fights
like you're still in school.

622
00:44:30,840 --> 00:44:32,190
Do you know that

623
00:44:33,030 --> 00:44:34,190
I don't like it at all

624
00:44:34,910 --> 00:44:36,520
when I see you get hurt?

625
00:44:40,620 --> 00:44:42,500
But after coming home to see you,

626
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:44,980
I've already forgotten

627
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:47,620
where it hurts.

628
00:45:06,140 --> 00:45:07,140
Saitharn...

629
00:45:09,300 --> 00:45:10,470
Don't disappear from me, okay?

630
00:46:07,270 --> 00:46:08,730
This is totally a tease.

631
00:46:44,910 --> 00:46:45,910
More...

632
00:47:47,270 --> 00:47:48,610
I love you, too.

633
00:48:21,100 --> 00:48:23,660
Today, we shall make Phusangdao Group

634
00:48:23,990 --> 00:48:26,200
remember our name, Khum Rimpha.

635
00:48:27,190 --> 00:48:30,380
Thank you for taking the time
to celebrate with us.

636
00:48:30,570 --> 00:48:32,080
You are so confident that

637
00:48:32,600 --> 00:48:35,790
good news
will come your way, are you not?

638
00:48:37,290 --> 00:48:38,220
Ms. Gale.

639
00:48:38,550 --> 00:48:40,780
There is a model we are unable to contact.

640
00:48:41,200 --> 00:48:42,460
I have no idea what happened.

